children.text: , commonly called Alt Text, is a hidden description of an image. It is read by screen readers or displayed on the screen when an image fails to load.
is to describe the important parts of an image to ensure that blind, low-vision, and other learners unable to visually access the image receive an equitable experience and dont miss key information.
should be applied to images in documents, presentation slides, course sites, or any other locations that contain visual information.
Describe only the relevant information in the image.

children.alternativeText: The photosynthesis equation shows that six carbon dioxide molecules and six water molecules produce one sugar molecule and one oxygen molecule. The sugar molecule is made of 6 carbons, 12 hydrogens, and 6 oxygens. Sunlight is used as an energy source.

children.text: Image from Concepts of Biology - 1st Canadian Edition by Charles Molnar and Jane Gair
A concise description helps highlight the important information in the image:

The photosynthesis equation shows that six carbon dioxide molecules and six water molecules produce one sugar molecule and one oxygen molecule. The sugar molecule is made of 6 carbons, 12 hydrogens, and 6 oxygens. Sunlight is used as an energy source.
Describe the aspects of the image that are important to the specific context in which youre using it

Include important text that appears in the image in the alt text description

children.text: Start descriptions with Image of or Picture of
Describe images that are purely decorative
Repeat information that appears elsewhere in the content
Editorialize or include your own feelings or opinions about the image
